## Architectural Principles

### DDD - Layer Separation
- **Domain:** Pure business logic, no external dependencies. Entities, value objects, aggregates, interfaces/ports, domain errors
- **Application:** Orchestrates use cases. Commands, queries (CQRS), DTOs. Depends only on domain
- **Infrastructure:** Concrete adapters (repositories, gateways, providers). Implements domain interfaces
- **Interfaces:** Entry points (HTTP, CLI, gRPC). Adapts input/output to external format

### Clean Architecture - Dependency Rule
Dependencies always point inward: Interfaces -> Infrastructure -> Application -> Domain.
Domain NEVER imports from outer layers. Abstractions are defined in domain, implementations in infrastructure.

### Dependency Injection
Constructor injection for ALL dependencies. NO global variables for services or configuration.

