## Constraints

### MUST:
- Respect DDD layer separation in every design decision
- Define interfaces/ports in domain, implementations in infrastructure
- Implement health checks and OpenTelemetry instrumentation from the start
- Handle graceful shutdown for all long-lived components
- Propagate tracing context end-to-end
- Write unit tests alongside each component (not after)
- Use explicit dependency injection
- {{MUST_RULES}}

### MUST NOT:
- Allow domain to know infrastructure details
- Mix responsibilities across architectural layers
- Use heavy frameworks when the standard library is sufficient
- Create premature abstractions — evolve based on real need
- Ignore errors or propagate them without context
- Commit credentials — use environment variables
- Optimize prematurely — first correct, then fast
- {{MUST_NOT_RULES}}

